Label: logical axiom
Definition: logical axiom is a rule defined in semantic model to allow for classification by automatic reasoners

Label: functional rule
Definition: a rule which details the specific action which should be performed when a number of conditions are met

Label: curation rule
Definition: a rule which explains how to perform a specific curation action (for instance, a numeric conversion or a string replacement)

Label: regular expression
Definition: A regular expression, regex or regexp (sometimes called a rational expression) is a sequence of characters that define a search pattern.

Label: mapping rule
Definition: a rule which explain how to relate one entity from a domain knowledge to another entity in another domain knowledge

Label: ontology tagged entity
Definition: a textual entity associated with a semantic annotation in the form of an identifier corresponding to a term in an ontology

Label: normalized textual entity
Definition: a textual entity which has been regularized through a curation process involving data transformation such as markup or substitution

Label: propriatory file format
Definition: a file format specification whose rights are only available to the owner and creator of the said specifications

Label: open file format
Definition: a file format whose specifications are available freely, with no restriction, allow full appraisal and review

Label: standard compliant file format
Definition: a file format which complies with a specification

Label: data standard
Definition: a data standard is a information content entity which prescribe syntax or semantic or both  for a given domain knowledge

Label: template
Definition: a standardized non-executable file type used by computer software as a pre-formatted example on which to base other files, especially documents

Label: transformation template
Definition: a template devised as a blueprint for operation such as extract transform load or similar data transformations

Label: metadata acquisition template
Definition: a template devised for a regularized collection of annotation.

Label: data acquisition template
Definition: a template devised for a regularized collection of annotated datasets

Label: RDF triple store
Definition: is a purpose-built database for the storage and retrieval of triples[1] through semantic queries. A triple is a data entity composed of subject-predicate-object, like "Bob is 35" or "Bob knows Fred".

Label: knowledge model
Definition: knowledge model is an information content entity which corresponds to a representation of domain of human

Label: object model
Definition: An entity‚Äìrelationship model (or ER model) describes interrelated things of interest in a specific domain of knowledge.

Label: uml model
Definition: an object model following unified modeling language formalization

Label: semantic data model
Definition: Semantic data model is a high-level semantics-based database description and structuring formalism (database model) for databases. This database model is designed to capture more of the meaning of an application environment than is possible with contemporary database models.

Label: statistical model
Definition: A statistical model is a mathematical model that embodies a set of statistical assumptions concerning the generation of sample data (and similar data from a larger population). A statistical model represents, often in considerably idealized form, the data-generating process.

Label: talend
Definition: a software suite for business intelligence, data wrangling and data mining

Label: tamr
Definition: a software service for performing curation services powered by machine learning techniques.

Label: trifacta
Definition: a software suite for business intelligence, data wrangling and data mining

Label: google refine
Definition: a software service for data curation and data cleanup provided by Google software company

Label: google bigtable
Definition: a software service for data storage and data mining provided by Google software company

Label: amazon comprehend
Definition: a software service for data curation and data cleaning provided by Amazon software company

Label: amazon redshift
Definition: a software service for data storage and data mining provided by Amazon software company

Label: microsoft azure
Definition: a software service for data storage and data mining provided by Microsoft software company and the Azure cloud solution

Label: tableau
Definition: a software service for performing ETL operations provided by software company Pentaho, a subsidiary of Hitachi.

Label: penthaho kettle
Definition: a software service for performing ETL operations provided by software company Pentaho, a subsidiary of Hitachi.

Label: sisense
Definition: a software suite for business intelligence, data wrangling and data mining

Label: elsevier
Definition: a software suite for business intelligence, data wrangling and data mining

Label: poolparty
Definition: a software service which offers support for semantic and knowledge management

Label: centinel
Definition: a software service provided by SciBite company to manage controlled terminologies and curation function, combining functions equivalent to OLS,zooma and oxo

Label: ontology lookup service
Definition: a software service provided by EMBL-EBI SOFT group, which serves controled terminologies, allowing searches and exploration and term selection.

Label: zooma
Definition: a software service provided bu EMBL-EBI SOFT group which assist curation based on prior of existing curated and annotated dataset from ArrayExpress database

Label: oxo
Definition: a software service provided bu EMBL-EBI SOFT group which serves mapping between ontologies

Label: ncbo bioportal
Definition: a software service provided by the National Center for Biomedical Ontologies, which serves controled terminologies, allowing searches and exploration and term selection.

Label: ncbo annotator
Definition: a software service provided by the National Center for Biomedical Ontologies which, given a body of text and a set of ontologies will return annotation hits.

Label: natural language processing
Definition: Natural language processing (NLP) is a process concerned with the interactions between computers and human (natural) languages, in particular how to program computers to process and analyze large amounts of natural language data.

Label: text mining
Definition: text mining is the process of deriving high-quality information from text. High-quality information is typically derived through the devising of patterns and trends

Label: sentence extraction
Definition: sentence extraction is a technique used for automatic summarization of a text. In this shallow approach, statistical heuristics are used to identify the most salient sentences of a text. Sentence extraction is a low-cost approach compared to more knowledge-intensive deeper approaches which require additional knowledge bases such as ontologies or linguistic knowledge. In short "sentence extraction" works as a filter which allows only important sentences to pass.

Label: string tokenization
Definition: string tokenization is the process of demarcating and possibly classifying sections of a string of input characters.

Label: concept recognition
Definition: the process of identifying an entity and marking it up from a free text input

Label: entity name recognition
Definition: Named-entity recognition (NER) (also known as entity identification, entity chunking and entity extraction) is a subtask of information extraction that seeks to locate and classify named entity mentions in unstructured text into pre-defined categories such as the person names, organizations, locations, medical codes, time expressions, quantities, monetary values, percentages,

Label: part of speech tagging
Definition: part-of-speech tagging (POS tagging or PoS tagging or POST), also called grammatical tagging or word-category disambiguation, is the process of marking up a word in a text (corpus) as corresponding to a particular part of speech,[1] based on both its definition and its context‚Äîi.e., its relationship with adjacent and related words in a phrase, sentence, or paragraph.

Label: information extraction
Definition: Information extraction (IE) is the task of automatically extracting structured information from unstructured and/or semi-structured machine-readable documents.

Label: information management
Definition: Information management (IM) concerns a cycle of organizational activity: the acquisition of information from one or more sources, the custodianship and the distribution of that information to those who need it, and its ultimate disposition through archiving or deletion.

Label: terminology management
Definition: the process of handling (from developing to maintaining and serving) controled vocabularies

Label: terminology hosting
Definition: the process of loading, serving controlled vocabularies and terminologies for access, browsing and selection

Label: terminology lookup
Definition: the process of searching a terminology with an input string for matching concepts

Label: ontology management
Definition: the process of handling (from developing to maintaining and serving) a formal knowledge representation, semantic artefact

Label: ontology lookup
Definition: the process of searching an ontology with an input string for matching concepts

Label: semantic tagging
Definition: the process of marking up free text element (tokens, possibly resulting from tokenization) with a controlled term from a semantic artefact

Label: semantic search
Definition: a search process which relies on ontology to improve retrieval (e.g. query expansion)

Label: ontology development
Definition: the process of creating, assembling a formal semantic representation

Label: ontology maintenance
Definition: the process of keeping a semantic representation up to date and in keeping with advances in the domain. This covers dealing with term submission, term obsoletion, release and evolution

Label: ontology refactoring
Definition: the process of re-arranging, re-engineering a formal semantic representation for optimization purpose, such as promotion of module reuse.

Label: ontology composition
Definition: the process of creating a formal semantic model from sets of existing modules extracted from other compatible semantic frameworks

Label: ontology extension
Definition: the process of augmenting a formal semantic model following batch submission of terms from a domain or modeling of a new domain of knowledge connex to the main them of the ontology

Label: ontology dynamic extension
Definition: an ontology extension process which happens on the fly, as users come up with the need. This is hard to accomplish as allowing user defined terms at will may lead to inconsistency and breakage.

Label: knowledge representation
Definition: the process of formally describing a domain of knowledge

Label: knowledge formalization
Definition: the process of breaking down a domain of knowledge according to rules

Label: axiomatic representation
Definition: the process of representing knowledge using formal rules, known as axiomsm, which allow automatic reasoning and solving

Label: data modeling
Definition: the process of developing a domain representation by analysing data.

Label: data model
Definition: a data model is an information content entity which denotes and describes a domain of knowledge

Label: model training
Definition: the process of involving statistical methods, machine learning procedure to build a model which can be used to analysis new datasets and draw conclusions from never seen before data.

Label: classification
Definition: the process of  classification is the process of identifying to which of a set of categories (sub-populations) a new observation belongs, on the basis of a training set of data containing observations (or instances) whose category membership is known

Label: data imputation
Definition: data imputation is the process of replacing missing data with substituted values.

Label: dealing with missing value
Definition: dealing with missing value is a process which aims to address the problems that occur when no data value is stored for the variable in an observation. Missing data are a common occurrence and can have a significant effect on the conclusions that can be drawn from the data.

Label: extract transform load process
Definition: extract, transform, load (ETL) is the general procedure of copying data from one or more sources into a destination system which represents the data differently from the source(s) or in a different context than the source(s).

Label: data type checking
Definition: the process of verifying that a data item supplied matches the specifications it is meant to comply with (e.g. an integer, a string,....)

Label: duplicate removal
Definition: the process of removing redundant entries which add volume without adding value

Label: data lookup
Definition: the process of assessing the presence of a data item in a existing data strucuture or data storage system

Label: characterset conversion
Definition: the process of changing the encoding of information from one repertoir of characters convention (characterset) to another one

Label: encoding conversion
Definition: the process of changing the encoding of information from one convention to another one

Label: numerical conversion
Definition: the process of changing a numerical representation

Label: date conversion
Definition: the process of changing a date representation from one convention to another (e.g. from free to ISO8601)

Label: unit conversion
Definition: the process of changing a numerical representation from one set of units to another one (e.g. from imperial to metric)

Label: field splitting
Definition: the process of dividing the information contained in one element into at least 2 more components

Label: field merging
Definition: the process of bringing information from at least 2 components into one single element (e.g concatenation operation)

Label: olap operation
Definition: online analytical processing is the process which concerns itself with analyzing multidimensional data interactively from multiple perspectives. OLAP consists of three basic analytical operations: consolidation (roll-up), drill-down, and slicing and dicing

Label: data cube pivoting
Definition: a subtype of olap operation which ...

Label: data cube slicing
Definition: a subtype of olap operation which ...

Label: data cube dicing
Definition: a subtype of olap operation which ...

Label: data integrity checking
Definition: Data integrity is the maintenance of, and the assurance of the accuracy and consistency of, data over its entire life-cycle,[1] and is a critical aspect to the design, implementation and usage of any system which stores, processes, or retrieves data.

Label: file checksumming
Definition: the process of computing a checksum of a digital document for the purpose of allowing data integrity checking during exchange and transmission

Label: encryption
Definition: the process of encoding digitical information to make it impossible to decipher without a key, known as the encryption key

Label: anonymization
Definition: Data anonymization is a type of information sanitization whose intent is privacy protection. It is the process of either encrypting or removing personally identifiable information from data sets, so that the people whom the data describe remain anonymous.

Label: pseudoanymization
Definition: Pseudonymization is a data management and de-identification procedure by which personally identifiable information fields within a data record are replaced by one or more artificial identifiers, or pseudonyms.

Label: mapping
Definition: data mapping is the process of creating data element mappings between two distinct data models. Data mapping is used as a first step for a wide variety of data integration tasks,

Label: automatic schema mapping
Definition: the process of using software agent to perform a mapping task between data models

Label: manual schema mapping
Definition: the process of using human expert to perform a mapping task between data models

Label: automatic ontology mapping
Definition: the process of using software agent to perform a mapping task between ontologies, semantic artefacts

Label: manual ology mapping
Definition: the process of using human expert to perform a mapping task between ontologies, semantic artefacts

Label: serialization
Definition: serialization (or serialisation) is the process of translating data structures or object state into a format that can be stored (for example, in a file or memory buffer) or transmitted (for example, across a network connection link) and reconstructed later (possibly in a different computer environment)

Label: format conversion
Definition: format conversion is a process on changing the representation model used during serialization

Label: assessment
Definition: the process of checking and evaluating

Label: validation
Definition: the process of checking against a set of rules and ensuring those are met

Label: syntactic validation
Definition: the process of checking against a set of rules which only concerns themselves with the grammar (syntax) but not the context. A syntactically valid document may contain incoherent content (semantic)

Label: semantic validation
Definition: the process of checking against a set of semantic rules to ascertain information content validity (rather than its format)

Label: constraint validation
Definition: the process of checking against a set of constraints

Label: compliance assessment
Definition: an assessment process which ascertain conformance to a set of specifications

Label: data hosting
Definition: the process of storing and serving data

Label: file hosting
Definition: the process of storing and serving files

Label: ontology hosting
Definition: the process of storing and serving semantic artefacts

Label: identifier management
Definition: the process of handling (minting, serving, deprecating, obsoleting) data item used to denotes and uniquely mark entities:

Label: identifier minting
Definition: the process of creating an identifier (e.g. DOI)

Label: identifier resolution
Definition: the process of handling a request formed from an identifier and direct the requesting agent to the relevant content

Label: identifier mapping
Definition: the process of provinding a correspondance between identifiers from 2 distinct resources for the equivalent entities

Label: identifier tombstoning
Definition: the process of leaving a marker in a location where a digital record has been withdrawn, in order to signify that the record had previously existed.

Label: data storage
Definition: the process of preserving data and information in digital form

Label: rdbms data storage
Definition: a data storage process which uses a relational database management system

Label: document oriented data storage
Definition: a data storage process which uses a storage system indexing document directly

Label: graph data storage
Definition: a data storage process which stored data as a graph based representation (in contrast to table based representation as in RDBMS)

Label: publication
Definition: the process of making a data object available to a public

Label: versioning
Definition: the process of handling managing the evolution and changes to a data object

Label: data assessment
Definition: an assessment process which focuses solely on data

Label: statistical assessment
Definition: an assessment process which relies on statistical methods and exploration to carry out an evaluation against a set of metrics

Label: domain expert assessment
Definition: an assessment process carried by a human agent whose domain knowledge is recognized

Label: collegial/community assessment
Definition: an assessment process carried by a group of human agent whose domain knowledge is recognized

Label: quality assessment
Definition: a process which aims to evaluate the quality of an entity

Label: quality assurance
Definition: a process in which the delivery of a service or the quality of a product is assessed, and compared with that required.

Label: licensing
Definition: a process of choosing or granting a license to an entity (software, hardware,data)

Label: maintenance
Definition: a process which aim to ensure continuation, persistance of a service or structure at minima to maintain its existence and availability.

Label: resource allocation
Definition: a process which defines how means are assigned to people or organization to execute a task

Label: value based assessment
Definition: a process which consists in estimating the performance of a process based on value addition generated by said process

Label: access condition
Definition: a rule deterrmine who, when, what and how entities may be made available.

Label: access protocol
Definition: an access protocol is a software specification defining the implementation for obtaining data under a number of access conditions

Label: ftp
Definition: file transfer protocol is a standard network protocol used for the transfer of computer files between a client and server on a computer network. FTP specifications evolved from the initial RFC114 from 1971 to the latest specification RFC2428 adding support for IPv6 in 1998.

Label: http
Definition: The Hypertext Transfer Protocol (HTTP) is an application protocol for distributed, collaborative, hypermedia information systems. HTTP is the foundation of data communication for the World Wide Web. It is an international standard specified by RFC 2068 in 1997 (HTTP1.1),  obsoleted by RFC 2616 in 1999, which was likewise replaced by the RFC 7230 family of RFCs in 2014.

Label: sftp
Definition: secure file transfer protocol is a secured version of the FTP procotol, which relies on SSH authentication

Label: application programming interface
Definition: An application programming interface (API) is a computing interface which defines interactions between multiple software intermediaries

Label: rest api
soap api
Definition: SOAP (abbreviation for Simple Object Access Protocol) is a messaging protocol specification for exchanging structured information in the implementation of web services in computer networks. Its purpose is to provide extensibility, neutrality, verbosity and independence.[vague] It uses XML Information Set for its message format, and relies on application layer protocols, most often Hypertext Transfer Protocol (HTTP), although some legacy systems communicate over Simple Mail Transfer Protocol (SMTP), for message negotiation and transmission

Label: open/smart api
Definition: The OpenAPI Specification, originally known as the Swagger Specification, is a specification for machine-readable interface files for describing, producing, consuming, and visualizing RESTful web services.

Label: graphql api
Definition: an API which is built using the GraphQL is a query language, a specification, and a set of tools that operates over a single endpoint using HTTP. It is meant to address the issue of "over and under fetching" during querying REST endpoints. GraphQL language was developed by Facebook. (https://www.howtographql.com/basics/1-graphql-is-the-better-rest/)

Label: maturity level
Definition: a quality to indicate the stage at which an entity is in its life cycle

Label: exploratory
Definition: a maturity level with indicates an early phase, for feasability study capability

Label: prototypic
Definition: a maturity level with indicates an early phase, for evaluation and testing assessment capability

Label: immature
Definition: a maturity level which indicates developing capability which has not reached full potential

Label: mature
Definition: a maturity level which indicates a stable, fully fledged capability

Label: production grade
Definition: a maturity level which indicates a stable, susceptible to be deployed in production environment capability

Label: state of the art
Definition: a maturity level which indicates a reference status for a capability in its domain.

Label: deployed
Definition: a maturity level which indicates a stable, susceptible to be deployed in production environment

Label: obsolescent
Definition: a maturity level which indicates declining capability

Label: obsolete
Definition: a maturity level which indicates a capability has reached the end of its life.

Label: retired
Definition: a maturity level which indicates a capability has been removed from frontline production.

Label: Maturity_Level_1
Definition: Data is managed as a requirement to support the analytical workflows of the project, focused on delivering its own results'

Label: Maturity_Level_2
Definition: Data is managed as a critical research data asset. Achieve a level of management that enables project to efficiently use and manipulate its data assets'

Label: Maturity_Level_3
Definition: Data is managed according to community standards with re-usability beyond the project scope in mind'

Label: Maturity_Level_4
Definition: Usability and Applicability of Data for use and re-use is measured against metrics to evaluate the implemented processes of the data management environment'

Label: Maturity_Level_5
Definition: The Environment processes are considered community best practices for FAIR data management'

Label: granularity level
Definition: a quality to indicate the size of the grain in the physical world. by abstraction, a quality to indicate how atomic an entity is.

Label: fine
Definition: a quality to indicate a small size of the entities making up an assembly.

Label: coarse
Definition: a quality to indicate a lack of refinement of the entities making up an assembly.

Label: intermediate
Definition: a quality to indicate the medium size of the entities making up an assembly.

Label: findability
Definition: a quality to indicate how easy or hard it is to locate/find an entity

Label: search engine referenced
Definition: a quality to indicate that an information entity is indexed by global search engines such as Bing,Google,Yandex,DuckDuckGo..)

Label: schema.org annotated
Definition: a quality to indicate that an information entity is markup with schema.org ontology terms

Label: deposited in public archive
Definition: a quality to indicate that an information entity is available from a data archive

Label: assigned with a persistent http resolveable identifier
Definition: a quality to indicate that an information entity is available from a data archive and has been assigned a persistent url

Label: doi-ed
Definition: a quality to indicate that an information entity metadata is conformant to datacite metadata schema and has been assigned a Digital Object Identifier (DOI)

Label: accessibility
Definition: a quality to indicate how easy or hard it is to understand how an entity may be access and then access it

Label: enclaved
Definition: a quality to indicate that no access to the entity is possible other than physical site visit

Label: access-controlled
Definition: a quality to indicate that the entity can only be accessed provided the necessary amount of credentials and authorization

Label: interoperability
Definition: a quality to indicate how systems are capable of interacting and working together automatically

Label: standard compliant
Definition: a quality which indicates the entity is conformant to an information specification

Label: standard certified
Definition: a quality which indicates the entity is conformant to an information specification as assessed by a certification body

Label: reusability
Definition: a quality to indicate how easy or hard it is to mobilize and reuse an information entity , for instance in the context of meta-analysis and data integration.

Label: data manager
Definition: a role to manage company/organization data to ensure security of electronic information related to the organisation and implement systems to offer efficient analysis, storage and documentation of company records. Reduce costs by identifying bad data practices and replacing them with improved practices.

Label: data steward
Definition: a data steward is a role within an organization responsible for utilizing an organization's data governance processes to ensure fitness of data elements - both the content and metadata.

Label: data analyst
Definition: the role of a personel in charge of performing computational or statistical analysis over company/organisation digital assets and datasets

Label: data custodian
Definition: A data custodian ensures that 1) Access to the data is authorized and controlled. 2)Data stewards are identified for each data set. 3)Technical processes sustain data integrity. 4)Processes exist for data quality issue resolution in partnership with Data Stewards. 5)Technical controls safeguard data. 6)Data added to data sets are consistent with the common data model. 7)Versions of Master Data are maintained along with the history of changes. 8)Change management practices are applied in maintenance of the database. 9)Data content and changes can be audited

Label: subject matter export
Definition: the role of a personal to bring expertice and knowledge in a specific domain

Label: chief information officer
Definition: the role of a personel in an organization/company to organization, oversee and decide on all tasks related to data and information management in said organization. The role involves taking executive decisions.

Label: scientist/researcher
Definition: the role of a personel in an organization/company to perform and carry out scientific research

Label: data scientist
Definition: the role of a personel in an organization/company in charge of performing data analysis and research with data, around data and about data to deliver scientific insight to the decision makers.

Label: decision maker
Definition: the role of a personel in an organization/company with the power of taking executive decisions

Label: IT provider
Definition: the role of an organization to deliver information technology services.

Label: data processor
Definition: the role of a personel in an organization to operate on data once clearance has been obtained from a data controller or data custodian

Label: data controller
Definition: the role of a personel to supervise, organize and manage protection and privacy of data.

Label: software engineer
Definition: the role of a personel to  conceive information technology solution and computer code in the form of deployable software.

Label: data curator
Definition: the role of a personel to preserve, annotate, archive digital assets produced or purchased by an organization.

Label: data management plan
Definition: a plan documenting the resources and practices, such as ontologies, data formats, information standards and backup, protection measures respectively with the objective of ensuring proper data management.

Label: curation policy
Definition: a document outlining the semantic resources, terminologies, controlled vocabularies and data format against which curation will be applied. Such document. also specifies the steps requires to version datasets following curation action.

Label: data dictionary
Definition: a data dictionnary is a document listing all the variables and their values sets for categorical variables or numerical ranges of values for continuous values, as well as associated units, formulas for computed derived variables, codes and rules for dealing with missing value.

Label: material transfer agreement
Definition: a material transfer agreement (MTA) is a contract that governs the transfer of tangible research materials between two organizations, when the recipient intends to use it for his or her own research purposes. It is usually legally binding and requires legal representatives of said organizations to supervised the writing and approval of the document.

Label: data access agreement
Definition: a data access agreement (DAA) is a document to specify the terms under which users are provided access to the specified data, and to obtain explicit acceptance of those terms by a user prior to granting him or her access to the data. It is usually legally binding and requires legal representatives of said organizations to supervised the writing and approval of the document

Label: availability
Definition: a quality to indicates if an entity can be obtained

Label: consistency
Definition: a quality to indicates if an enttity is coherent, without discrepancies

Label: CURATO_denotes_maturity_of
Definition: a relation between a maturity indicator and a process

Label: CURATO_complies_with
Definition: a relation holding between a information entity and data format specification

Label: CURATO_formalized_as
Definition: a relation holding between an information content entity and a data model

Label: CURATO_implements
Definition: a relation holding between a software or a template and domain-specific annotation requirements

Label: CURATO_implemented_by
Definition: a relation holding between a domain-specific annotation requirement and software or template

Label: CURATO_performed_using
Definition: a relation holding between a process of validation and rule

Label: CURATO_defined_by
Definition: a relation holding between a process of validation and rule

Label: CURATO_available_from
Definition: a relation holding between a domain-specific annotation requirement and website

Label: CURATO_defines
Definition: a relation holding between a  rule and a domain specific annotation requirement

Label: CURATO_conforms_to
Definition: a relation holding between a file format and a file format specification

Label: CURATO_certified_by
Definition: a relation holding between a certification and an organization

Label: certification
Definition: a process in which a process is certified to comply against a set of specifications

Label: INSTANCE_metric_F+S02
Definition: Data is reported by following community specific minimum information guidelines (an instance of metric generated by FAIRplus)
